Scott,

I'll send you an email with access to create posts.

In the mean time, here's a few development ideas the steering
committee has discussed...these ideas/concepts might be beneficial to
Refresh Denver and/or the community at large:

-featured member of the month; a page highlighting a Denver Refresher,
their talents, their skills, their site, their recent project, etc.
-a members area for allowing users to create profiles; this then could
be used for networking and collaborating on projects (e.g., I need to
search for designers, flash designers, database developers, and SEO
specialists to help me with my latest project.)
-a search tool for the community to find qualified talent (i.e., a way
to search the profiles much like the previous networking tool)

There's been some other talked about ideas such as providing a
repository of free templates (see http://www.oswd.org/ for an example)
thus in effect providing a service to the community.

Anyway, as you can imagine there's a lot that we could do to make
Refresh Denver great.  What idea's do you have?

Matthew

