<POSTDATE> 2007-10-02T12:22:00 </POSTDATE>
That seems like a lot of structure to maintain.

Can't we get the same effect relying on the Google Group and scraping
the site and newsletter? It seems to work well for Refresh Phoenix.

I'm interested in a light-weight, high signal-to-noise resource.

As for meetings, I think there should be a monthly meeting scheduled
at one well known location at a well known time. Somebody should
probably be responsible for setting a meeting theme or topic.

As far as I'm concerned, the location should be:
- public access - no security to go through and locked doors to
manage
- open WiFi
- comfortable chairs and tables
- food and drink [alcohol not necessary - a coffee shop would be
fine]
- inexpensive - preferably free
- projection display a plus, but not mandatory.

I'll contribute to discussions and show up at meetings. I can probably
talk about something occationally.

thanks,
Mike

